# SkyGuardwall — Windsurf Cascade Rules

You are an expert Go and React developer working on SkyGuardwall — a Docker host-network firewall management tool that reads iptables/nftables/ss from the host machine and provides a React web UI for port exposure analysis and firewall rule management.

## Tech Stack

- Backend: Go 1.22+, Gin, GORM, golang-jwt/jwt v5, log/slog
- Frontend: React 18, TypeScript strict, Vite, Ant Design 5.x, Zustand, Axios
- Database: GORM + modernc.org/sqlite (default) / MySQL / PostgreSQL
- Deploy: Docker host network, single port 8080, go:embed

## Project Layout

```
cmd/server/main.go           # Entry point + go:embed
internal/handler/            # Gin handlers — HTTP binding only
internal/service/            # Business logic + exec.CommandContext
internal/service/parser/     # Pure parsers: ss, iptables, nft
internal/model/              # GORM structs (NO foreign keys)
internal/database/db.go      # Multi-DB init + AutoMigrate
internal/router/router.go    # All routes
frontend/src/api/client.ts   # Axios + Bearer interceptor
frontend/src/store/auth.ts   # Zustand auth state
frontend/src/pages/          # Dashboard Ports Iptables Nft Firewall Login
```

## Architecture

```
Browser → :8080
  /api/v1/*  → JWT middleware → Handler → Service → exec/GORM
  /*         → Gin serves embedded React SPA (go:embed frontend/dist)
```

No Nginx. No separate frontend server. One binary, one port.

## Non-Negotiable Rules

### Database
- NEVER add foreign key constraints — no `gorm:"foreignKey:..."`, `References:`, `constraint:`
- GORM AutoMigrate only — no raw DDL
- Works on SQLite / MySQL / PostgreSQL without schema changes

### Backend Go
- Handlers: HTTP binding + response only. No exec, no business logic.
- Services: all logic, all `exec.CommandContext` calls
- Allowed exec commands only: `iptables`, `iptables-save`, `ip6tables`, `ss`, `nft`, `ip`
- All iptables write inputs validated: IP/CIDR, port 0–65535, action in {ACCEPT,DROP,REJECT}
- Unified response: `{"code":0,"message":"success","data":{...}}`
- Log writes with slog.Info; never log passwords or tokens

### Frontend TypeScript
- All API calls through `src/api/client.ts` (Axios instance). Never `fetch()`.
- Named exports only. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore`.
- Ant Design only — no mixing UI libraries
- Token in localStorage key `sgw_token`; 401 → redirect to /login + clear token

### Docker
- `network_mode: host` + `privileged: true` — required
- Single service, no sidecars
- `CGO_ENABLED=0` (modernc.org/sqlite is pure-Go)
- Runtime image needs: iptables ip6tables nftables iproute2

## Dev Commands

```bash
go mod tidy && go run ./cmd/server
cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev
npm run build --prefix frontend && go build -o sky-guardwall ./cmd/server
docker compose up --build
```

## Do NOT

- Add foreign keys or `REFERENCES` to any model
- Use `bash -c` or shell with user-controlled strings
- Call exec in handlers
- Add dependencies without checking go.mod / package.json first
- Add new Docker services
- Use `fetch()` in React components
- Write raw SQL
